        "ai_gen_block_46f1420_CdznXd": {
          "type": "ai_gen_block_46f1420",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "About",
            "description": "<p>Marie-Louise Müller is a slow fashion designer from Hessen, based in Berlin since 2018. She completed her BA in Fashion Design at Atelier Chardon Savard in 2025. As a designer, she approaches her work through a slow fashion lens rooted in handcraft techniques like crochet, knitting, embroidery and hand-sewing.<\/p><p>By working exclusively with natural fibers and upcycling techniques, her ambition is to consistantly create thoughtful and conceptual designs that meets evolving demands on sustainable practices while standing out with a defined personality.<\/p><p>Müller’s work has been showcased at Der Berliner Salon (twice in 2025), Fashion Positions (2025), and awarded Best Craftsmanship at Neo.Fashion (2024). These milestones, along with multiple press features, have established her as an emerging voice and cemented the dedication to core slow fashion values.<\/p>",
            "image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/linkedin03.png",
            "button_text": "Learn more",
